{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904143536,"sessionID":"ses_283ddf084ffeVDO3EJ8GNUANRn","part":{"id":"prt_d7c22b88a001a6P9MyGigdBHDO","messageID":"msg_d7c22a15f001AaF4O1lVR4kQNq","sessionID":"ses_283ddf084ffeVDO3EJ8GNUANRn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e491b6a54165494b883b3f8c81f9223a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n6: \n7: | Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n8: |--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n9: | `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n10: | `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n11: | `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n12: | `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Directory Structure\n19: \n20: ```\n21: cmd/\n22: ├── picod/\n23: │   ├── main.go              # PicoD entry point (implemented)\n24: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n25: ├── router/\n26: │   ├── main.go              # Router entry point\n27: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n28: ├── workloadmanager/\n29: │   ├── main.go              # WorkloadManager entry point\n30: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n31: └── agentd/\n32: │   ├── main.go              # Agentd entry point\n33: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Binary Dependency Graph\n37: \n38: ```\n39: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                            CLI Binaries                                       │\n41: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n42: │                                                                               │\n43: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n44: │   │   picod   │     │   router  │     │workloadmanager│     │  agentd   │   │\n45: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n46: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n47: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n48: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n49: │   │ pkg/picod │     │pkg/router │     │pkg/workload   │     │pkg/agentd │   │\n50: │   │           │     │           │     │   manager     │     │           │   │\n51: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n52: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n53: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n54: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n55: │   │                    Common Dependencies                                 │ │\n56: │   │  - k8s.io/klog/v2 (logging)                                           │ │\n57: │   │  - github.com/spf13/pflag (flags)                                     │ │\n58: │   │  - context, os, signal                                                │ │\n59: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: │                                                                               │\n61: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Deployment Model\n65: \n66: ```\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n69: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n70: │                                                                  │\n71: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n72: │  │ router Deployment│    │workloadmanager   │                  │\n73: │  │    (Pod :8080)   │───▶│ Deployment       │                  │\n74: │  └──────────────────┘    │   (Pod :8080)    │                  │\n75: │           │              └──────────────────┘                  │\n76: │           │                      │                              │\n77: │           ▼                      ▼                              │\n78: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n79: │  │ Redis/Valkey     │    │  K8s API Server  │                  │\n80: │  │ (Session Store)  │    │  (CRDs, Pods)    │                  │\n81: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘                  │\n82: │                                                                  │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n84: │  │ agentd Deployment│    (Leader Election enabled)             │\n85: │  │  (Controller)    │                                           │\n86: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n87: │                                                                  │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: \n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                      Sandbox Pod                                 │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n94: │  │ picod sidecar    │    (Local code execution)                │\n95: │  │   (Port 8080)    │                                           │\n96: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### Common CLI Configuration Pattern\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: package main\n108: \n109: type CLIConfig struct {\n110:     LogLevel    string `flag:\"log-level\" default:\"info\" usage:\"Log level (debug, info, warn, error)\"`\n111:     MetricsAddr string `flag:\"metrics-addr\" default:\"0\" usage:\"Metrics server address (0 to disable)\"`\n112:     HealthAddr  string `flag:\"health-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Health check server address\"`\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### PicoD CLI Configuration\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: package main\n120: \n121: type PicoDConfig struct {\n122:     CLIConfig\n123:     Port         int    `flag:\"port\" default:\"8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n124:     Workspace    string `flag:\"workspace\" default:\"\" usage:\"Workspace directory path\"`\n125:     AuthEnabled  bool   `flag:\"auth-enabled\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable authentication\"`\n126:     MaxExecTime  int    `flag:\"max-exec-time\" default:\"30\" usage:\"Maximum execution time in seconds\"`\n127:     MaxFileSize  int64  `flag:\"max-file-size\" default:\"10485760\" usage:\"Maximum file size in bytes\"`\n128:     SanitizeRoot string `flag:\"sanitize-root\" default:\"\" usage:\"Root directory for path sanitization\"`\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Router CLI Configuration\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: package main\n136: \n137: type RouterConfig struct {\n138:     CLIConfig\n139:     Port                 string `flag:\"port\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n140:     MaxConcurrentRequests int   `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"1000\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent requests\"`\n141:     Debug                bool   `flag:\"debug\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable debug mode\"`\n142:     EnableTLS            bool   `flag:\"enable-tls\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable TLS\"`\n143:     TLSCert              string `flag:\"tls-cert\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS certificate file\"`\n144:     TLSKey               string `flag:\"tls-key\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS key file\"`\n145:     StoreAddr            string `flag:\"store-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey address\"`\n146:     StorePassword        string `flag:\"store-password\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey password\"`\n147:     StoreType            string `flag:\"store-type\" default:\"redis\" usage:\"Store type (redis, valkey)\"`\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### WorkloadManager CLI Configuration\n152: \n153: ```go\n154: package main\n155: \n156: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n157:     CLIConfig\n158:     Addr              string        `flag:\"addr\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP server address\"`\n159:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"read-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP read timeout\"`\n160:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration `flag:\"write-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP write timeout\"`\n161:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"idle-timeout\" default:\"90s\" usage:\"HTTP idle timeout\"`\n162:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration `flag:\"shutdown-timeout\" default:\"10s\" usage:\"Graceful shutdown timeout\"`\n163:     GCInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"gc-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Garbage collection interval\"`\n164:     GCOnceTimeout     time.Duration `flag:\"gc-once-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"Single GC run timeout\"`\n165:     Kubeconfig        string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n166:     MasterURL         string        `flag:\"master-url\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes API server URL\"`\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Agentd CLI Configuration\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: package main\n174: \n175: type AgentdConfig struct {\n176:     CLIConfig\n177:     IdleThreshold        time.Duration `flag:\"idle-threshold\" default:\"30m\" usage:\"Idle threshold for cleanup\"`\n178:     CheckInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"check-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Cleanup check interval\"`\n179:     MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"10\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent cleanups\"`\n180:     Namespaces           []string      `flag:\"namespace\" default:\"default\" usage:\"Namespaces to watch\"`\n181:     LeaderElection       bool          `flag:\"leader-election\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable leader election\"`\n182:     LeaderElectionID     string        `flag:\"leader-election-id\" default:\"agentcube-agentd\" usage:\"Leader election ID\"`\n183:     Kubeconfig           string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## API Contracts\n190: \n191: ### Binary Entry Point Interface\n192: \n193: Each binary follows this pattern:\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: package main\n197: \n198: type Binary interface {\n199:     InitFlags() *Config\n200:     ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error\n201:     Run(ctx context.Context, cfg *Config) error\n202:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n203: }\n204: \n205: func main() {\n206:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n207:     flag.Parse()\n208:     \n209:     cfg := InitFlags()\n210:     if err := ValidateConfig(cfg); err != nil {\n211:         klog.Fatalf(\"invalid config: %v\", err)\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214:     \n215:     ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n216:     defer cancel()\n217:     \n218:     if err := Run(ctx, cfg); err != nil {\n219:         klog.Fatalf(\"run error: %v\", err)\n220:         os.Exit(1)\n221:     }\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ### Signal Handling Contract\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: package main\n229: \n230: func setupSignalHandler() context.Context {\n231:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n232:     \n233:     c := make(chan os.Signal, 2)\n234:     signal.Notify(c, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n235:     \n236:     go func() {\n237:         sig := <-c\n238:         klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n239:         cancel()\n240:         \n241:         if sig == syscall.SIGKILL {\n242:             <-c\n243:             klog.InfoS(\"received second signal, forcing exit\")\n244:             os.Exit(1)\n245:         }\n246:     }()\n247:     \n248:     return ctx\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Health Check Contract\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: package main\n256: \n257: type HealthChecker interface {\n258:     Live() bool\n259:     Ready() bool\n260: }\n261: \n262: func (h *HealthServer) Start(addr string) error {\n263:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n264:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/live\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n265:         if h.Live() {\n266:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n267:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n268:         } else {\n269:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n270:         }\n271:     })\n272:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/ready\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n273:         if h.Ready() {\n274:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n275:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n276:         } else {\n277:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n278:         }\n279:     })\n280:     return http.ListenAndServe(addr, mux)\n281: }\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### Flag Registration Contract\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: package main\n288: \n289: func InitFlags() *Config {\n290:     cfg := &Config{}\n291:     \n292:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n293:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n294:     \n295:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LogLevel, \"log-level\", \"info\", \"Log level\")\n296:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.MetricsAddr, \"metrics-addr\", \"0\", \"Metrics address\")\n297:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.HealthAddr, \"health-addr\", \"\", \"Health address\")\n298:     \n299:     flag.Parse()\n300:     \n301:     return cfg\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Binary Implementation Details\n308: \n309: ### 1. picod (cmd/picod/main.go)\n310: \n311: **Purpose**: Local code execution daemon running as a sidecar in sandbox pods.\n312: \n313: **Current Implementation** (pkg/picod/server.go:26-77):\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: func main() {\n317:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n318:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n319: \n320:     port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"HTTP listening port\")\n321:     workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Workspace directory path\")\n322:     flag.Parse()\n323: \n324:     config := &picod.Config{\n325:         Port:      *port,\n326:         Workspace: *workspace,\n327:     }\n328: \n329:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n330:     if err != nil {\n331:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)\n332:         os.Exit(1)\n333:     }\n334: \n335:     if err := server.Run(context.Background()); err != nil {\n336:         klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n337:         os.Exit(1)\n338:     }\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Endpoints**:\n343: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n344: |------|--------|---------|\n345: | `/health` | GET | Health check |\n346: | `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code |\n347: | `/api/files` | POST | Upload file |\n348: | `/api/files` | GET | List files |\n349: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file |\n350: \n351: ### 2. router (cmd/router/main.go)\n352: \n353: **Purpose**: Session routing and reverse proxy for agent/code interpreter invocations.\n354: \n355: **Implementation Template**:\n356: \n357: ```go\n358: func main() {\n359:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n360:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n361:     \n362:     cfg := &RouterConfig{}\n363:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Port, \"port\", \":8080\", \"HTTP listening port\")\n364:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreAddr, \"store-addr\", \"\", \"Redis/Valkey address\")\n365:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreType, \"store-type\", \"redis\", \"Store type\")\n366:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests, \"max-concurrent\", 1000, \"Max concurrent requests\")\n367:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.Debug, \"debug\", false, \"Enable debug mode\")\n368:     flag.Parse()\n369:     \n370:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n371:     \n372:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n373:     if err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376:     \n377:     sessionManager := router.NewSessionManager(store)\n378:     jwtManager := router.NewJWTManager()\n379:     \n380:     server := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n381:         Port:                 cfg.Port,\n382:         MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n383:         Debug:                cfg.Debug,\n384:     }, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, klog.Logger{})\n385:     \n386:     if err := server.Start(ctx); err != nil {\n387:         klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)\n388:     }\n389: }\n390: ```\n391: \n392: **Endpoints**:\n393: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n394: |------|--------|---------|\n395: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n396: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n397: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy |\n398: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy |\n399: \n400: ### 3. workloadmanager (cmd/workloadmanager/main.go)\n401: \n402: **Purpose**: Workload manager HTTP server for sandbox lifecycle management.\n403: \n404: **Implementation Template**:\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: func main() {\n408:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n409:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n410:     \n411:     cfg := &WorkloadManagerConfig{}\n412:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Addr, \"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n413:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.ReadTimeout, \"read-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Read timeout\")\n414:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.WriteTimeout, \"write-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Write timeout\")\n415:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.GCInterval, \"gc-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"GC interval\")\n416:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Kubeconfig path\")\n417:     flag.Parse()\n418:     \n419:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n420:     \n421:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(cfg.Kubeconfig, cfg.MasterURL)\n422:     if err != nil {\n423:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n424:     }\n425:     \n426:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n427:     if err != nil {\n428:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(\n432:         workloadmanager.Config{\n433:             Addr:            cfg.Addr,\n434:             ReadTimeout:     cfg.ReadTimeout,\n435:             WriteTimeout:    cfg.WriteTimeout,\n436:             ShutdownTimeout: cfg.ShutdownTimeout,\n437:         },\n438:         klog.Logger{},\n439:         k8sClient,\n440:         store,\n441:     )\n442:     \n443:     server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n444:     server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(k8sClient, store))\n445:     \n446:     server.GracefulShutdown()\n447:     \n448:     errCh := server.Start()\n449:     select {\n450:     case err := <-errCh:\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"workloadmanager error: %v\", err)\n452:     case <-ctx.Done():\n453:         server.Stop(context.Background())\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: **Endpoints**:\n459: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n460: |------|--------|---------|\n461: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n462: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n463: | `/sandboxes` | POST | Create sandbox |\n464: | `/sandboxes/:id` | GET | Get sandbox |\n465: | `/sandboxes/:id` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n466: \n467: ### 4. agentd (cmd/agentd/main.go)\n468: \n469: **Purpose**: Kubernetes controller for idle resource cleanup using controller-runtime.\n470: \n471: **Implementation Template**:\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func main() {\n475:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n476:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n477:     \n478:     cfg := &AgentdConfig{}\n479:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.IdleThreshold, \"idle-threshold\", 30*time.Minute, \"Idle threshold\")\n480:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.CheckInterval, \"check-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"Check interval\")\n481:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup, \"max-concurrent\", 10, \"Max concurrent cleanups\")\n482:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.LeaderElection, \"leader-election\", true, \"Enable leader election\")\n483:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LeaderElectionID, \"leader-election-id\", \"agentcube-agentd\", \"Leader election ID\")\n484:     flag.Parse()\n485:     \n486:     k8sConfig, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n487:     if err != nil {\n488:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to get k8s config: %v\", err)\n489:     }\n490:     \n491:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(k8sConfig, ctrl.Options{\n492:         LeaderElection:          cfg.LeaderElection,\n493:         LeaderElectionID:        cfg.LeaderElectionID,\n494:         LeaderElectionNamespace: \"default\",\n495:     })\n496:     if err != nil {\n497:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create manager: %v\", err)\n498:     }\n499:     \n500:     if err := agentd.SetupIdleCleanupController(mgr, cfg); err != nil {\n501:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup controller: %v\", err)\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     klog.InfoS(\"starting agentd controller\")\n505:     if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n506:         klog.Fatalf(\"controller error: %v\", err)\n507:     }\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ---\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Categories\n516: \n517: | Category | Description | Action |\n518: |----------|-------------|--------|\n519: | `ErrConfigInvalid` | Configuration validation failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n520: | `ErrStoreConnect` | Store connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n521: | `ErrK8sConnect` | Kubernetes connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n522: | `ErrServerStart` | HTTP server start failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n523: | `ErrSignalReceived` | Graceful shutdown triggered | Log info, cancel context |\n524: | `ErrShutdownTimeout` | Shutdown exceeded timeout | Log warning, force exit |\n525: \n526: ### Error Handling Pattern\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: func handleStartupError(component string, err error) {\n530:     if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n531:         klog.InfoS(\"shutdown requested\")\n532:         return\n533:     }\n534:     \n535:     if errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGTERM) || errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGINT) {\n536:         klog.InfoS(\"received termination signal\", \"signal\", err)\n537:         return\n538:     }\n539:     \n540:     klog.ErrorS(err, \"startup failure\", \"component\", component)\n541:     os.Exit(1)\n542: }\n543: ```\n544: \n545: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n546: \n547: ```\n548: 1. Signal received (SIGTERM/SIGINT)\n549: 2. Cancel main context\n550: 3. Stop accepting new requests\n551: 4. Wait for in-flight requests (timeout configurable)\n552: 5. Close store connections\n553: 6. Close K8s client connections\n554: 7. Exit with code 0\n555: ```\n556: \n557: ### Validation Errors\n558: \n559: ```go\n560: func ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error {\n561:     if cfg.Port <= 0 || cfg.Port > 65535 {\n562:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid port: %d\", cfg.Port)\n563:     }\n564:     \n565:     if cfg.IdleThreshold < 0 {\n566:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid idle threshold: %v\", cfg.IdleThreshold)\n567:     }\n568:     \n569:     if cfg.CheckInterval < 0 {\n570:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid check interval: %v\", cfg.CheckInterval)\n571:     }\n572:     \n573:     if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup < 0 {\n574:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid max concurrent cleanup: %d\", cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup)\n575:     }\n576:     \n577:     return nil\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Testing Strategy\n584: \n585: ### Unit Tests\n586: \n587: #### Flag Parsing Tests\n588: \n589: ```go\n590: func TestInitFlags(t *testing.T) {\n591:     tests := []struct {\n592:         name     string\n593:         args     []string\n594:         expected *Config\n595:     }{\n596:         {\n597:             name: \"default values\",\n598:             args: []string{},\n599:             expected: &Config{\n600:                 Port:           8080,\n601:                 LogLevel:       \"info\",\n602:                 IdleThreshold:  30 * time.Minute,\n603:             },\n604:         },\n605:         {\n606:             name: \"custom port\",\n607:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\"},\n608:             expected: &Config{\n609:                 Port:          9000,\n610:             },\n611:         },\n612:         {\n613:             name: \"multiple flags\",\n614:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\", \"-debug\", \"true\"},\n615:             expected: &Config{\n616:                 Port:  9000,\n617:                 Debug: true,\n618:             },\n619:         },\n620:     }\n621:     \n622:     for _, tt := range tests {\n623:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n624:             fs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"test\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n625:             cfg := &Config{}\n626:             setupFlags(fs, cfg)\n627:             \n628:             err := fs.Parse(tt.args)\n629:             require.NoError(t, err)\n630:             \n631:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expected.Port, cfg.Port)\n632:         })\n633:     }\n634: }\n635: ```\n636: \n637: #### Signal Handler Tests\n638: \n639: ```go\n640: func TestSignalHandler(t *testing.T) {\n641:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n642:     \n643:     syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n644:     \n645:     select {\n646:     case <-ctx.Done():\n647:         assert.True(t, true)\n648:     case <-time.After(5 * time.Second):\n649:         t.Fatal(\"signal handler did not cancel context\")\n650:     }\n651: }\n652: ```\n653: \n654: #### Config Validation Tests\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func TestValidateConfig(t *testing.T) {\n658:     tests := []struct {\n659:         name        string\n660:         config      *Config\n661:         expectError bool\n662:     }{\n663:         {\n664:             name: \"valid config\",\n665:             config: &Config{\n666:                 Port:          8080,\n667:                 IdleThreshold: 30 * time.Minute,\n668:             },\n669:             expectError: false,\n670:         },\n671:         {\n672:             name: \"invalid port\",\n673:             config: &Config{\n674:                 Port: -1,\n675:             },\n676:             expectError: true,\n677:         },\n678:         {\n679:             name: \"invalid idle threshold\",\n680:             config: &Config{\n681:                 IdleThreshold: -1 * time.Minute,\n682:             },\n683:             expectError: true,\n684:         },\n685:     }\n686:     \n687:     for _, tt := range tests {\n688:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n689:             err := ValidateConfig(tt.config)\n690:             if tt.expectError {\n691:                 assert.Error(t, err)\n692:             } else {\n693:                 assert.NoError(t, err)\n694:             }\n695:         })\n696:     }\n697: }\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ### Integration Tests\n701: \n702: #### Binary Startup Tests\n703: \n704: ```go\n705: func TestBinaryStartup(t *testing.T) {\n706:     if testing.Short() {\n707:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n708:     }\n709:     \n710:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"picod\")\n711:     \n712:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \"18080\")\n713:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n714:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n715:     \n716:     err := cmd.Start()\n717:     require.NoError(t, err)\n718:     \n719:     defer cmd.Process.Kill()\n720:     \n721:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n722:         resp, err := http.Get(\"http://localhost:18080/health\")\n723:         if err != nil {\n724:             return false\n725:         }\n726:         defer resp.Body.Close()\n727:         return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n728:     }, 10*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n729: }\n730: ```\n731: \n732: #### Graceful Shutdown Tests\n733: \n734: ```go\n735: func TestGracefulShutdown(t *testing.T) {\n736:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"router\")\n737:     \n738:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \":18080\", \"-store-type\", \"memory\")\n739:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n740:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n741:     \n742:     err := cmd.Start()\n743:     require.NoError(t, err)\n744:     \n745:     waitForHealthy(t, \"http://localhost:18080/health/live\")\n746:     \n747:     syscall.Kill(cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGTERM)\n748:     \n749:     done := make(chan error, 1)\n750:     go func() {\n751:         done <- cmd.Wait()\n752:     }()\n753:     \n754:     select {\n755:     case err := <-done:\n756:         assert.NoError(t, err)\n757:     case <-time.After(15 * time.Second):\n758:         t.Fatal(\"binary did not shutdown within timeout\")\n759:     }\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: ### Build Tests\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: func TestBuildAllBinaries(t *testing.T) {\n767:     binaries := []string{\"picod\", \"router\", \"workloadmanager\", \"agentd\"}\n768:     \n769:     for _, binary := range binaries {\n770:         t.Run(binary, func(t *testing.T) {\n771:             cmd := exec.Command(\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", \"/tmp/\"+binary, \"./cmd/\"+binary)\n772:             output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n773:             assert.NoError(t, err, \"build output: %s\", output)\n774:             \n775:             assert.FileExists(t, \"/tmp/\"+binary)\n776:         })\n777:     }\n778: }\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ---\n782: \n783: ## Metrics\n784: \n785: ### Prometheus Metrics\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: var (\n789:     startupDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n790:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_startup_duration_seconds\",\n792:             Help: \"Time taken for binary startup\",\n793:         },\n794:         []string{\"binary\"},\n795:     )\n796:     \n797:     shutdownDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n798:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n799:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_shutdown_duration_seconds\",\n800:             Help: \"Time taken for graceful shutdown\",\n801:         },\n802:         []string{\"binary\"},\n803:     )\n804:     \n805:     configReloadCount = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n806:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n807:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_config_reload_total\",\n808:             Help: \"Number of configuration reloads\",\n809:         },\n810:         []string{\"binary\"},\n811:     )\n812: )\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ---\n816: \n817: ## Configuration\n818: \n819: ### Environment Variables\n820: \n821: | Variable | Binary | Purpose |\n822: |----------|--------|---------|\n823: | `PORT` | picod, router, workloadmanager | HTTP port override |\n824: | `WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n825: | `STORE_ADDR` | router, workloadmanager | Redis/Valkey address |\n826: | `STORE_TYPE` | router, workloadmanager | Store backend type |\n827: | `KUBECONFIG` | workloadmanager, agentd | Kubernetes config path |\n828: | `LOG_LEVEL` | all | Log level override |\n829: \n830: ### Command-Line Flags Summary\n831: \n832: | Flag | Default | Purpose |\n833: |------|---------|---------|\n834: | `-port` | 8080 | HTTP listening port |\n835: | `-workspace` | current dir | Workspace directory (picod) |\n836: | `-idle-threshold` | 30m | Idle cleanup threshold (agentd) |\n837: | `-check-interval` | 5m | Cleanup check interval (agentd) |\n838: | `-leader-election` | true | Enable leader election (agentd) |\n839: | `-kubeconfig` | in-cluster | Kubernetes config path |\n840: | `-debug` | false | Enable debug mode (router) |\n841: | `-metrics-addr` | 0 | Prometheus metrics address |\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Build Configuration\n846: \n847: ### Go Module\n848: \n849: ```go\n850: // go.mod\n851: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n852: \n853: go 1.24\n854: \n855: require (\n856:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.x\n857:     github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.x\n858:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.x\n859:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.x\n860: )\n861: ```\n862: \n863: ### Makefile Targets\n864: \n865: ```makefile\n866: .PHONY: build clean\n867: \n868: build:\n869: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n870: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n871: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n872: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n873: \n874: clean:\n875: \trm -rf bin/\n876: \n877: build-picod:\n878: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n879: \n880: build-router:\n881: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n882: \n883: build-workloadmanager:\n884: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n885: \n886: build-agentd:\n887: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ### Docker Build\n891: \n892: ```dockerfile\n893: # Dockerfile for picod\n894: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n895: WORKDIR /app\n896: COPY . .\n897: RUN go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n898: \n899: FROM alpine:3.19\n900: COPY --from=builder /picod /picod\n901: ENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n902: ```\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## Implementation Checklist\n907: \n908: - [x] `cmd/picod/main.go` - PicoD entry point (implemented)\n909: - [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` - Router entry point\n910: - [ ] `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` - WorkloadManager entry point\n911: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` - Agentd entry point\n912: - [ ] Common signal handling package\n913: - [ ] Common flag validation utilities\n914: - [ ] Health check server integration\n915: - [ ] Metrics server integration\n916: - [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing\n917: - [ ] Unit tests for config validation\n918: - [ ] Integration tests for binary startup\n919: - [ ] Integration tests for graceful shutdown\n920: - [ ] Makefile build targets\n921: - [ ] Docker build configurations\n922: - [ ] Helm deployment manifests\n923: \n924: ---\n925: \n926: ## Dependencies\n927: \n928: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n929: |---------|---------|---------|\n930: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n931: | `github.com/spf13/pflag` | v1.x | POSIX/GNU-style flags |\n932: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities (agentd) |\n933: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.x | HTTP framework (picod, router) |\n934: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | v5.x | HTTP framework (workloadmanager) |\n935: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |\n\n(End of file - total 935 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n|--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n| `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n| `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n| `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n| `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775904143527,"end":1775904143533}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904143550,"sessionID":"ses_283ddf084ffeVDO3EJ8GNUANRn","part":{"id":"prt_d7c22b4cf001yzjflD5yqsx0hp","messageID":"msg_d7c22a15f001AaF4O1lVR4kQNq","sessionID":"ses_283ddf084ffeVDO3EJ8GNUANRn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f989745fdf164771a2c2f59e14fa2600","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 实现基于时间触发的 Sandbox 垃圾回收机制，自动清理过期和空闲的 Sandbox 资源，防止集群资源累积和膨胀。GC 作为后台 goroutine 运行，提供 TTL 强制执行、空闲超时清理、批量处理限制和可配置的时间间隔。\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                        HTTPServer                               │\n22: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n23: │  │                SandboxLifecycleManager                   │   │\n24: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │   │\n25: │  │  │  K8sClient  │  │ MemoryStore  │  │ LifecycleConfig│  │   │\n26: │  │  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │   │\n27: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n28: │                           │                                     │\n29: │                           │ delegation                          │\n30: │                           ▼                                     │\n31: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n32: │  │                   GarbageCollector                       │   │\n33: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │   │\n34: │  │  │                   runLoop                          │ │   │\n35: │  │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────┐  │ │   │\n36: │  │  │  │ time.Ticker  │──│ runOnce (per cycle)        │  │ │   │\n37: │  │  │  └──────────────┘  │ ┌────────────────────────┐ │  │ │   │\n38: │  │  │                    │ │ListExpiredSandboxes    │ │  │ │   │\n39: │  │  │                    │ │ListInactiveSandboxes   │ │  │ │   │\n40: │  │  │                    │ │DeleteSandbox (batched) │ │  │ │   │\n41: │  │  │                    │ └────────────────────────┘ │  │ │   │\n42: │  │  │                    └────────────────────────────┘  │ │   │\n43: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │   │\n44: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │   │\n45: │  │  │   Start()  │  │    Stop()       │  │ GetStats()   │ │   │\n46: │  │  └────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └──────────────┘ │   │\n47: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │   │\n48: │  │  │SetIdleTimeout() ←─ runtime config via idleMu       │ │   │\n49: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │   │\n50: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Component Relationships\n55: \n56: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n57: |-----------|------|--------------|\n58: | `GarbageCollector` | Periodic cleanup executor | `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store` |\n59: | `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Deletion delegate | `K8sClient`, `Store` |\n60: | `MemoryStore` | Sandbox metadata storage | `sync.RWMutex` |\n61: | `runLoop` | Background goroutine ticker loop | `time.Ticker`, `stopCh` |\n62: | `runOnce` | Single GC cycle logic | `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes` |\n63: \n64: ### GC Execution Flow\n65: \n66: ```\n67: Start() → wg.Add(1) → go runLoop()\n68:                             │\n69:                             ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n70:                             ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n71:                             └── for {\n72:                                   select {\n73:                                     case <-stopCh: return\n74:                                     case <-ticker.C: runOnce(ctx)\n75:                                   }\n76:                                 }\n77: \n78: runOnce(ctx)\n79:   │\n80:   ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n81:   ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n82:   ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, now.Add(-idleTimeout), GCBatchSize)\n83:   └── for sb in expired + inactive:\n84:         │\n85:         ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n86:         │     ├── GetSandboxBySessionID → NotFoundError? return\n87:         │     ├── K8sClient.Delete(SandboxGVR)\n88:         │     ├── K8sClient.Delete(SandboxClaimGVR) [if SandboxClaimKind]\n89:         │     └── Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n90:         │\n91:         ├── NotFoundError? continue (ignore)\n92:         ├── Other error? log + continue\n93:         └── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n94:             logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n95: \n96: Stop() → close(stopCh) → wg.Wait()\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Dependencies\n100: \n101: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n102: |---------|---------|-------------|\n103: | `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles | `context` (stdlib) |\n104: | `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency | `sync` (stdlib) |\n105: | `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing | `time` (stdlib) |\n106: | `types` | SandboxInfo struct | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n107: | `apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n108: | `metav1` | DeleteOptions | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` |\n109: \n110: ## Data Structures\n111: \n112: ### Core Types\n113: \n114: #### GarbageCollector Struct\n115: \n116: ```go\n117: type GarbageCollector struct {\n118:     manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager  // Deletion delegate\n119:     interval    time.Duration             // GC cycle interval (default: 2m)\n120:     onceTimeout time.Duration             // Single cycle timeout (default: 2m)\n121:     stopCh      chan struct{}             // Graceful shutdown signal\n122:     wg          sync.WaitGroup            // Goroutine synchronization\n123:     logger      Logger                    // Structured logging\n124:     idleTimeout time.Duration             // Idle sandbox threshold (default: 15m)\n125:     idleMu      sync.RWMutex              // Protects idleTimeout concurrent access\n126: }\n127: ```\n128: \n129: **Field Responsibilities:**\n130: \n131: | Field | Type | Purpose |\n132: |-------|------|---------|\n133: | `manager` | `*SandboxLifecycleManager` | Delegates `DeleteSandbox` for actual cleanup |\n134: | `interval` | `time.Duration` | Ticker interval between GC cycles |\n135: | `onceTimeout` | `time.Duration` | Context timeout for single `runOnce` execution |\n136: | `stopCh` | `chan struct{}` | Closed on `Stop()` to signal shutdown |\n137: | `wg` | `sync.WaitGroup` | Ensures goroutine completes before `Stop()` returns |\n138: | `logger` | `Logger` | Logs GC events (deletions, errors, shutdown) |\n139: | `idleTimeout` | `time.Duration` | Threshold for inactive sandbox detection |\n140: | `idleMu` | `sync.RWMutex` | Protects `idleTimeout` for runtime config changes |\n141: \n142: #### GarbageCollectorStats Struct\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: type GarbageCollectorStats struct {\n146:     Interval    time.Duration  // Current GC cycle interval\n147:     OnceTimeout time.Duration  // Current single-cycle timeout\n148:     IdleTimeout time.Duration  // Current idle threshold\n149: }\n150: ```\n151: \n152: #### Store Interface Extensions\n153: \n154: ```go\n155: type Store interface {\n156:     // ... existing methods ...\n157:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n158:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: **New Method Semantics:**\n163: \n164: | Method | Input | Output | Purpose |\n165: |--------|-------|--------|---------|\n166: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `before` timestamp, `limit` | Sandboxes with `ExpiresAt < before` | TTL-based cleanup candidates |\n167: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `before` timestamp, `limit` | Sandboxes with `LastActivity < before` | Idle timeout cleanup candidates |\n168: \n169: #### MemoryStore Implementation\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: type MemoryStore struct {\n173:     mu              sync.RWMutex\n174:     sandboxes       map[string]*types.SandboxInfo  // sessionID → SandboxInfo\n175:     expirationIndex map[string]time.Time           // sandboxID → ExpiresAt\n176: }\n177: \n178: func (s *MemoryStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(_ context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n179:     s.mu.RLock()\n180:     defer s.mu.RUnlock()\n181: \n182:     var expired []*types.SandboxInfo\n183:     for _, sandbox := range s.sandboxes {\n184:         if sandbox.ExpiresAt.Before(before) {\n185:             expired = append(expired, sandbox)\n186:         }\n187:     }\n188: \n189:     // Sort by ExpiresAt ascending (oldest first)\n190:     sort.Slice(expired, func(i, j int) bool {\n191:         return expired[i].ExpiresAt.Before(expired[j].ExpiresAt)\n192:     })\n193: \n194:     // Truncate to limit\n195:     if limit > 0 && len(expired) > limit {\n196:         expired = expired[:limit]\n197:     }\n198: \n199:     return expired, nil\n200: }\n201: \n202: func (s *MemoryStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(_ context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n203:     s.mu.RLock()\n204:     defer s.mu.RUnlock()\n205: \n206:     var inactive []*types.SandboxInfo\n207:     for _, sandbox := range s.sandboxes {\n208:         // Skip sandboxes with zero LastActivity (newly created)\n209:         if !sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() && sandbox.LastActivity.Before(before) {\n210:             inactive = append(inactive, sandbox)\n211:         }\n212:     }\n213: \n214:     // Sort by LastActivity ascending (most inactive first)\n215:     sort.Slice(inactive, func(i, j int) bool {\n216:         return inactive[i].LastActivity.Before(inactive[j].LastActivity)\n217:     })\n218: \n219:     // Truncate to limit\n220:     if limit > 0 && len(inactive) > limit {\n221:         inactive = inactive[:limit]\n222:     }\n223: \n224:     return inactive, nil\n225: }\n226: ```\n227: \n228: #### DeletionReason Constants\n229: \n230: ```go\n231: type DeletionReason string\n232: \n233: const (\n234:     DeletionReasonIdleTimeout        DeletionReason = \"IdleTimeout\"\n235:     DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached DeletionReason = \"MaxDurationReached\"\n236:     DeletionReasonUserRequest        DeletionReason = \"UserRequest\"\n237: )\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### LifecycleConfig GC Fields\n241: \n242: ```go\n243: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n244:     DefaultTTL          time.Duration  // Default sandbox TTL (8h)\n245:     DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration  // Default idle threshold (15m)\n246:     DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration  // Max session duration (8h)\n247:     GCInterval          time.Duration  // GC cycle interval (2m)\n248:     GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration  // Single GC cycle timeout (2m)\n249:     DeletionGracePeriod int64          // K8s deletion grace period (0)\n250:     DeletionTimeout     time.Duration  // Single deletion timeout (30s)\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### Constants\n255: \n256: ```go\n257: // pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go\n258: const (\n259:     GCBatchSize               = 16                    // Max sandboxes per GC cycle per category\n260:     GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute       // Default GC cycle interval\n261:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute      // Default idle timeout threshold\n262:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour         // Default sandbox TTL\n263:     SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second      // Single deletion timeout\n264: )\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ## API Contracts\n268: \n269: ### Constructor\n270: \n271: ```go\n272: func NewGarbageCollector(\n273:     manager *SandboxLifecycleManager,\n274:     interval time.Duration,\n275:     onceTimeout time.Duration,\n276:     logger Logger\n277: ) *GarbageCollector\n278: ```\n279: \n280: **Behavior:**\n281: - If `interval == 0`, defaults to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2m)\n282: - If `onceTimeout == 0`, defaults to `2 * time.Minute`\n283: - Initializes `idleTimeout` from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n284: - Creates `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n285: \n286: ### Lifecycle Methods\n287: \n288: ```go\n289: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start()\n290: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop()\n291: ```\n292: \n293: **Start() Contract:**\n294: - Calls `gc.wg.Add(1)`\n295: - Launches `go gc.runLoop()`\n296: - Returns immediately (non-blocking)\n297: \n298: **Stop() Contract:**\n299: - Calls `close(gc.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n300: - Calls `gc.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n301: - Returns only after goroutine exits\n302: \n303: ### Core Logic Methods\n304: \n305: ```go\n306: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runLoop()\n307: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error\n308: ```\n309: \n310: **runLoop() Contract:**\n311: - Runs in separate goroutine\n312: - Executes `runOnce(ctx)` immediately on start\n313: - Creates `ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n314: - Loops on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n315: - On `stopCh`, logs `\"garbage collector stopped\"` and returns\n316: - On `ticker.C`, calls `runOnce(context.Background())`\n317: - Defers `gc.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n318: \n319: **runOnce(ctx) Contract:**\n320: - Creates `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)`\n321: - Returns error if `ListExpiredSandboxes` fails\n322: - Returns error if `ListInactiveSandboxes` fails\n323: - Processes at most `GCBatchSize` expired + `GCBatchSize` inactive sandboxes\n324: - Ignores `NotFoundError` (sandbox already deleted)\n325: - Logs other errors but continues processing\n326: - Logs successful deletions with reason\n327: \n328: ### Runtime Configuration Methods\n329: \n330: ```go\n331: func (gc *GarbageCollector) SetIdleTimeout(timeout time.Duration)\n332: func (gc *GarbageCollector) getIdleTimeout() time.Duration\n333: func (gc *GarbageCollector) GetStats() GarbageCollectorStats\n334: ```\n335: \n336: **SetIdleTimeout(timeout) Contract:**\n337: - Acquires `gc.idleMu.Lock()`\n338: - Updates `gc.idleTimeout`\n339: - Releases mutex\n340: \n341: **getIdleTimeout() Contract:**\n342: - Acquires `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n343: - Returns current `gc.idleTimeout`\n344: - Releases mutex\n345: \n346: **GetStats() Contract:**\n347: - Acquires `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n348: - Returns `GarbageCollectorStats{Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout}`\n349: - Releases mutex\n350: \n351: ### Helper Functions\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: func determineDeletionReason(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, now time.Time, idleTimeout time.Duration) DeletionReason\n355: ```\n356: \n357: **Contract:**\n358: - If `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`: return `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n359: - If `!sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero()` AND `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`: return `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n360: - Otherwise: return `DeletionReasonUserRequest`\n361: \n362: ## Error Handling\n363: \n364: ### Error Categories\n365: \n366: | Error Type | Source | Handling |\n367: |------------|--------|----------|\n368: | `NotFoundError` | Store lookup, K8s delete | Silently ignored (already deleted) |\n369: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` error | Store query | Logged, `runOnce` returns error |\n370: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` error | Store query | Logged, `runOnce` returns error |\n371: | `DeleteSandbox` error (non-NotFound) | Lifecycle manager | Logged, continue to next sandbox |\n372: | K8s API error | Dynamic client | Wrapped in `InternalError` or `ConflictError` |\n373: \n374: ### Error Flow\n375: \n376: ```\n377: runOnce(ctx)\n378:   │\n379:   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes returns error?\n380:   │     └── logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n381:   │     └── return err  [stop cycle]\n382:   │\n383:   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes returns error?\n384:   │     └── logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n385:   │     └── return err  [stop cycle]\n386:   │\n387:   └── for each sandbox in expired + inactive:\n388:         │\n389:         ├── DeleteSandbox returns *NotFoundError?\n390:         │     └── continue  [ignore, already deleted]\n391:         │\n392:         ├── DeleteSandbox returns other error?\n393:         │     └── logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)\n394:         │     └── continue  [process remaining sandboxes]\n395:         │\n396:         └── DeleteSandbox succeeds?\n397:               └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ### Timeout Handling\n401: \n402: | Timeout | Default | Purpose | Mechanism |\n403: |---------|---------|---------|-----------|\n404: | `onceTimeout` | 2m | Prevent GC cycle from hanging | `context.WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)` |\n405: | `DeletionTimeout` | 30s | Prevent single deletion from hanging | `context.WithTimeout(ctx, config.DeletionTimeout)` |\n406: | `interval` | 2m | GC cycle frequency | `time.NewTicker(interval)` |\n407: \n408: ### Graceful Degradation\n409: \n410: - GC continues processing remaining sandboxes even if some deletions fail\n411: - NotFound errors are treated as success (resource already cleaned)\n412: - List errors abort the cycle but don't crash the GC\n413: - GC restarts on next ticker cycle after errors\n414: \n415: ## Testing Strategy\n416: \n417: ### Unit Tests (garbage_collector_test.go)\n418: \n419: | Test | Scenario | Verification |\n420: |------|----------|--------------|\n421: | `TestNewGarbageCollector` | Constructor with explicit values | Fields set correctly |\n422: | `TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval` | Constructor with zero values | Defaults applied |\n423: | `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` | Lifecycle management | Start launches goroutine, Stop waits for completion |\n424: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired` | Expired sandbox cleanup | Expired deleted, active remains |\n425: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive` | Idle timeout cleanup | Inactive deleted, active remains |\n426: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit` | Batch size enforcement | At most 16 deleted per category |\n427: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError` | Error resilience | All sandboxes processed |\n428: | `TestGarbageCollector_GetStats` | Stats retrieval | Correct values returned |\n429: | `TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce` | Concurrent safety | No race conditions |\n430: \n431: ### Test Setup Pattern\n432: \n433: ```go\n434: func setupTestGC(t *testing.T) (*GarbageCollector, *MemoryStore) {\n435:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n436:     dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n437:     informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n438: \n439:     k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n440:         dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n441:         coreClient:      fakeClient,\n442:         informerFactory: informerFactory,\n443:     }\n444: \n445:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n446:     logger := &mockLogger{}\n447:     config := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n448: \n449:     manager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n450:     gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n451: \n452:     return gc, store\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Mock Logger\n457: \n458: ```go\n459: type mockLogger struct{}\n460: \n461: func (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {}\n462: func (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {}\n463: ```\n464: \n465: ### Integration Tests (integration_test.go)\n466: \n467: | Test | Scenario | Verification |\n468: |------|----------|--------------|\n469: | Full GC flow | Create expired sandbox → run GC | Sandbox deleted from store and K8s |\n470: | Multiple cycles | 20+ expired sandboxes | GC processes across multiple cycles |\n471: | Lifecycle integration | Server start/stop | GC lifecycle bound to server |\n472: \n473: ### Test Coverage Goals\n474: \n475: | Area | Target Coverage |\n476: |------|------------------|\n477: | `garbage_collector.go` | >80% |\n478: | `store.go` (GC methods) | >80% |\n479: | `lifecycle.go` (`determineDeletionReason`) | 100% |\n480: \n481: ### Validation Commands\n482: \n483: ```bash\n484: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -v -run GarbageCollector\n485: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -coverprofile=coverage.out\n486: go tool cover -func=coverage.out\n487: go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager\n488: golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager\n489: ```\n490: \n491: ## Validation Checklist\n492: \n493: - [x] `GarbageCollector` struct defined with all required fields\n494: - [x] `NewGarbageCollector` constructor with default fallbacks\n495: - [x] `Start()` launches background goroutine\n496: - [x] `Stop()` signals shutdown and waits for completion\n497: - [x] `runLoop` uses ticker for periodic execution\n498: - [x] `runOnce` has context timeout protection\n499: - [x] `ListExpiredSandboxes` queries expired by `ExpiresAt`\n500: - [x] `ListInactiveSandboxes` queries inactive by `LastActivity`\n501: - [x] Batch limit (`GCBatchSize=16`) enforced per query\n502: - [x] NotFound errors silently ignored\n503: - [x] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n504: - [x] `determineDeletionReason` categorizes deletions correctly\n505: - [x] `SetIdleTimeout` runtime configuration supported\n506: - [x] `GetStats` returns current configuration\n507: - [x] `idleMu` protects concurrent `idleTimeout` access\n508: - [x] Store interface includes GC query methods\n509: - [x] `MemoryStore` implements GC query methods\n510: - [x] `LifecycleConfig` includes GC parameters\n511: - [x] `DefaultLifecycleConfig` provides GC defaults\n512: - [x] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n513: - [x] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n514: - [x] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n515: - [x] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n516: \n517: ## Open Questions\n518: \n519: - Q: Should GC metrics be exported to Prometheus?\n520:   - A: Deferred to future enhancement. Current implementation uses structured logging only.\n521: \n522: - Q: How should distributed GC work with multiple workload-manager instances?\n523:   - A: Deferred. Leader election can be added when HA deployment is required.\n524: \n525: - Q: Should `LastActivity` be updated on heartbeat or only on user actions?\n526:   - A: Updated on user actions (sandbox creation, heartbeat API calls). The heartbeat handler updates `LastActivity`.\n527: \n528: ## References\n529: \n530: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Implementation\n531: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - Test coverage\n532: - `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - `DeleteSandbox` delegation, `determineDeletionReason`\n533: - `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` - `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n534: - `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Store interface, `DeletionReason` constants\n535: - `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Timeout constants\n536: - Kubernetes TTL Controller: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/\n\n(End of file - total 536 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现基于时间触发的 Sandbox 垃圾回收机制，自动清理过期和空闲的 Sandbox 资源，防止集群资源累积和膨胀。GC 作为后台 goroutine 运行，提供 TTL 强制执行、空闲超时清理、批量处理限制和可配置的时间间隔。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md","time":{"start":1775904143524,"end":1775904143546}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775904143579,"sessionID":"ses_283ddf084ffeVDO3EJ8GNUANRn","part":{"id":"prt_d7c22b8bd0014jFh1dqO2OCIz6","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7c22a15f001AaF4O1lVR4kQNq","sessionID":"ses_283ddf084ffeVDO3EJ8GNUANRn","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":37617,"input":1388,"output":134,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":36095}},"cost":0}}
